    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-19T00:26:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-19T00:26:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/12–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Norway</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d86fn1">Sent also to Copenhagen <gloss target="#t_niact1"
                            >niact</gloss> as 510 and repeated for information to Paris as <gloss
                            target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 504.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-19T00:26:00-05:00"
                            >December 19, 1951—12:26 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>505. Re <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Election: <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> concerned re <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>’s report
                        (<gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 724 from Paris rptd info Oslo 50
                    and Copenhagen 37, Dec 18) Dels of Norway and Denmark do not have authority
                    switch from Byelorussia to Greece if election deadlock continues. <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> strongly desires election of Greece during
                    next balloting and requests you approach <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> soonest and express hope its Del will be given authority
                    vote for Greece during next balloting which we understand will take place Dec
                    20. Suggest you point out as appropriate arguments mentioned <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 369 to Copenhagen rptd Oslo 358, Oct
                        29,<note n="2" xml:id="d86fn2">See footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_89">p.
                            89</ref>.</note> and necessity resolving deadlock to permit SO to
                    function as of Jan 1.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
